The paper deals with the application of Graph Convolutional Neural Networks (GCNNs) to biomedical knowledge graphs, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. The paper also introduces a regularized attention mechanism to GCNNs, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The use of noisy data in KGs is a major challenge, which is addressed in the paper, making it relevant to the database (cs.DB) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
